         <div type="entry">
            <pb facs="https://leaf.bucknell.edu/sites/default/files/2026-01/diary58.jpg"/>
            <dateline>Tuesday 15.</dateline>
            <p>I have been under the weather and staid in my tent all day. This morning I felt
               pretty bright but towards evening the head-ache came again &amp; this evening I
               consulted the Doctor again, who gave me a prescription with directions to take
               it tomorrow if I could sleep to night. My appetite is extraordinaly good. Gen
               Reno with 3 regts from here 21st Mass, 51st N.Y. &amp; 48 Penn go to Roanoke
               tomorrow where they take on 3 regts &amp; go some place else. Though the news
               of the defeat at Corinth is here, yet our Generals think this is the most
               critical point of the War. The senseless cry against McClellan is creating
               alarm, Burnside, Reno, Parke &amp; Foster say that they will resign the day
               they hear that McClellan is removed.</p>
         </div>
